'''Rachel bas-Cohain''' (1937-1982), born and died in New York.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://americanart.si.edu/artist/rachel-bas-cohain-272|title=Smithsonian Art Museum|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> was a conceptual artist. In 1972, she was one of the founding members of [[A.I.R. Gallery]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=Alternative Art New York, 1965-1985 (Cultural Politics)|last=Ault|first=Julie|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> She described her work as "air, fluids, light in motion exhibited as sculpture."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article/1970/11/19/critics-reviewers-ignore-womans-art-show/|title=Critics, Reviewers Ignore Woman's Art Show|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
