'''Termination for Medical Reasons '''(TFMR) is a campaign and support group seeking to change the law in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] to allow [[abortion|terminations]] in cases of fatal foetal abnormalities. Amanda Mellet (of [[Mellet v Ireland]]) is a founding member.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Irish Times|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/life-and-style/people/i-believe-in-a-loving-god-and-that-i-won-t-be-damned-for-what-i-did-1.502988|page=13|title='I believe in a loving God and that I won't be damned for what I did'|first=Kathy|last=Sheridan|date=17 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Irish Independent|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/couple-to-file-un-petition-after-being-forced-to-travel-for-abortion-29749581.html|title=Couple to file UN petition after being forced to travel for abortion|first=Sam|last=Griffin|date=13 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Irish Independent|date=17 December 2014|first=Freya|last=Drohan|title=Parents of aborted baby: ‘It’s very hard for us not to be cynical’ about Varadkar’s claims|url=http://www.independent.ie/life/family/parenting/parents-of-aborted-baby-its-very-hard-for-us-not-to-be-cynical-about-varadkars-claims-30844231.html}}</ref>

==Campaigns==
They campaign for better services for people who experience fatal foetal abnormalities. In 2016 they welcomed the Irish government's new guidelines on [[bereavement counselling]] for grieving parents.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Irish Times|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/new-guidelines-for-grieving-parents-welcomed-1.2751389|title=New guidelines for grieving parents welcomed|first=Vivienne|last=Clarke|date=10 August 2016}}</ref>

==Initial meeting with politicians==

In April 2012, TFMR met with a group of 25 [[Teachta Dála|TDs]] and [[Seanad Éireann|Senators]] who were investigating how to reply the [[European Court of Human Rights]] judgement in [[A, B and C v Ireland]], and to ask for a change in Ireland's abortion law. Senator [[Rónán Mullen]], who was in attendance, was not sympathetic to their cause,<ref>{{cite tweet|title=@CoraSherlock @kencurtin @MagicMumCom it is not a claim it was indeed Ronan Mullen|date=21 April 2012|user=TFMRIRE|number=193687994757160960}}</ref> asking what their real agenda was.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=193732169863143426|user=TFMRIRE|title=fyi re senetor ronan mullen his words were "you have a bigger agenda dont you" nasty comment to someone who had just lost their child END OF|date=21 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Broadsheet.ie|url=http://www.broadsheet.ie/2012/04/21/the-nasty-td-the-smirking-senator/|date=21 April 2012|title=The Nasty TD…The Smirking Senator}}</ref><ref>{{cite episode|series=The Late Late Show|series-link=The Late Late Show (Irish TV series)|station=[[RTÉ One]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kgq8xUYYFvk|title=TFMR The Late late Show April 20 2012|date=20 April 2012|access-date=19 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.magicmum.com/phpBB/viewtopic.php?f=182&t=424465&start=24#p4919042|date=19 April 2012|title=MagicMum.com - View topic - FineGael TD : Fornication main cause of unwanted pregnancy|website=MagicMum.com|quote=He told me i {{sic|should of}} carried my baby till the end because Ireland has the best Palletive care in the world, he also said that he was sponosoring some child in africa that had one of the conditions that the other girl Ruths baby had. Then he asked one of us at the end of our session with them on the quiet he said "what is your :bomb: :bomb: :bomb: real agenda here?" this was to a girl who lost her daughter Aoife at 22 weeks}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Irish Times|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/system-ignores-and-stigmatises-women-who-travel-for-abortion-1.502569|title=System 'ignores and stigmatises' women who travel for abortion|first=Kathy|last=Sheridan|date=17 April 2012|page=1}}</ref> He later denied being nasty to the women.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=TheJournal.ie|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/ronan-mullen-horrified-at-nasty-suggestions-over-abortion-debate-424919-Apr2012/|date=21 April 2012|title=Ronan Mullen horrified at ‘nasty’ suggestions over abortion debate|first=Sinead|last=O'Carroll}}</ref>

==Protection of Life During Pregnancy Act 2013==
{{see also|Protection of Life During Pregnancy Act 2013}}

During the debate on the [[Protection of Life During Pregnancy Act 2013]], the group called for an exception to allow termination in cases of fatal foetal abnormalities,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/call-for-fatal-foetal-abnormalities-amendment-to-bill-1.1443325|title=Call for fatal foetal abnormalities amendment to Bill|first=Mary|last=Minihan|newspaper=[[The Irish Times]]|date=26 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Irish Independent|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/call-on-fatal-foetal-abnormalities-29375216.html|title=Call on fatal foetal abnormalities|date=26 June 2013}}</ref> however [[Taoiseach]] [[Enda Kenny]] claimed it would be unconstitutional to include that.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Irish Times|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/oireachtas/unconstitutional-to-include-fatal-foetal-abnormalities-in-legislation-taoiseach-says-1.1443863|title=Unconstitutional to include fatal foetal abnormalities in legislation, Taoiseach says|first=Marie|last=O'Halloran|date=26 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Irish Independent|url=http://www.independent.ie/irish-news/taoiseach-refuses-to-change-abortion-law-to-cover-fatal-foetal-abnormality-29376139.html|title=Taoiseach refuses to change abortion law to cover fatal foetal abnormality|first=Michael|last=Brennan|date=27 June 2013}}</ref>

==Citizens' Assembly==
{{see also|Citizens' Assembly (Ireland)}}

In 2016 the Irish government set up a Citizens' Assembly to discuss [[Abortion in the Republic of Ireland|Ireland's abortion laws]]. TFMR made a submission calling for a repeal of the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|Eighth Amendment]] and the removal of abortion from criminal law.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repealeight.ie/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/TFMR-Ireland.pdf|title=TFMR Ireland Submission to the Citizens' Assembly|date=14 December 2016|publisher=Termination for Medical Reasons}}</ref>{{rp|p6}}

They were not invited to present to the Citizens' Assembly. [[Every Life Counts]], a similar support/campaign group for parents of children disagnosed with fatal foetal abnormalities, but who are opposed to change in Ireland's abortion law, were invited.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.citizensassembly.ie/en/News/17-Advocacy-Groups-to-Address-Citizens-Assembly-on-the-Topic-of-Eighth-Amendment.html|title=17 Advocacy Groups to Address Citizens' Assembly on the Topic of Eighth Amendment|date=21 February 2017|publisher=[[Citizens' Assembly (Ireland)|Citizens' Assembly]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishmirror.ie/lifestyle/health/bereaved-parents-who-lost-babies-9919830|title=Bereaved parents who lost babies due to fatal foetal abnormalities excluded from speaking at sitting of the Citizens’ Assembly|date=26 February 2017|first=Slyvia|last=Pownall|newspaper=Irish Mirror}}</ref>

